<h2>What the industry needs</h2>

<p>
  The Tesla Optimus program is one of 29 active humanoid robotics initiatives. Every one of them faces
  the same behavioral challenges:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>Teleoperation-to-autonomy transitions without behavioral safety layers</li>
  <li>Motion execution without stability-aware conscience rules</li>
  <li>Demo environments that mask operational fragility</li>
  <li>No longitudinal behavioral monitoring across deployments</li>
</ul>

<p>
  These are not hardware problems. They are not perception problems. They are identity problems. The
  robot doesn't know what it is (teleoperated or autonomous), what it should refuse to do (motions that
  compromise stability), or how to represent itself honestly (control mode transparency).
</p>

<p>
  The Identity Stack provides all three. Eight files. Portable across bodies. Auditable by humans.
  Enforceable by machines.
</p>

